---
import Site from "../layouts/Site.astro";
import TuiFrame from "../components/TuiFrame.astro";
---

<Site
  title="how it works"
  description="fedit is built as an Elm-style update loop. Pure Model, pure update, effects on the thread pool, piece-table buffers, ANSI screen renderer."
  image="/og/how.png"
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container stack stack--lg">
      <div class="section__head">
        <h1>how it works</h1>
        <p class="section__lede">
          An Elm-style update loop. Pure model, pure update, one effect interpreter that folds its
          results back into the loop as messages.
        </p>
      </div>

      <section>
        <p class="arch-p">
          The <code>Model</code> is pure data. <code>Editor.update</code> is a pure function that takes
          a <code>Msg</code> and returns a new model plus a list of effects. <code>runEffect</code> is
          the only impure code path — it does file I/O and folds its result back into the loop as another
          <code>Msg</code>. <code>Layout.render</code> projects the model to a <code>Screen</code>,
          and
          <code>Renderer.render</code> writes that grid as ANSI escapes.
        </p>

        <TuiFrame label="data flow"><Fragment
          set:html={`                        +----------------------+
                        |        Model         |
                        |  workspace . tree    |
                        |  buffers + cursors   |
                        |  focus, theme,       |
                        |  panels, terminal    |
                        +-----+----------+-----+
                              |          |
              read by         |          |     read by
        +---------------------+          +---------------------+
        |                                                      |
        v                                                      v
+-----------------+                                  +-------------------+
|  <span class="accent">Editor.update</span>  |                                  |   <span class="accent">Layout.render</span>   |
|     (pure)      |                                  |      (pure)       |
+--------+--------+                                  +---------+---------+
         |                                                     |
   (model', effects)                                        Screen
         |                                                     |
         v                                                     v
+-----------------+                                  +-------------------+
|    runEffect    |                                  |  <span class="accent">Renderer.render</span>  |
|    (impure)     |                                  |   ANSI escapes    |
|  ScanWorkspace  |                                  +---------+---------+
|  LoadFile       |                                            |
|  SaveBuffer     |                                            v
+--------+--------+                                     terminal output
         |
         v
        Msg  ----------> dispatch &lt;---------- KeyPressed / Resize
                            ^                       (main loop)
                            |
                       feeds back`}
        /></TuiFrame>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>buffer storage</h2>
        <p class="arch-p">
          Text buffers use a piece table. The original file contents stay in one string, inserted
          text is appended to another string, and the visible document is represented as a list of
          pieces. Inserts and deletes stay local to the piece list while preserving enough state for
          undo and redo snapshots.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>files and encoding</h2>
        <p class="arch-p">
          Files are read as UTF-8. The line ending of the loaded file (<code>LF</code> or <code
            >CRLF</code
          >) is detected and reused on save; the buffer always works in <code>\n</code> form internally.
          Saving writes UTF-8 without a byte-order mark.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>concurrency</h2>
        <p class="arch-p">
          The workspace scan, file open, file save, clipboard, and config writes all run on the
          thread pool via <code>Task.Run</code>. The main loop drains a <code
            >ConcurrentQueue&lt;Msg&gt;</code
          > of completed effects each tick, so input never blocks behind I/O. <code
            >ScanWorkspace</code
          > and <code>LoadFile</code> each carry a single <code>CancellationTokenSource</code> so a second
          invocation drops the previous result.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>further reading</h2>
        <p class="arch-p">
          The full architecture overview, including module dependency order and the <code>Msg</code>
          / <code>Effect</code> taxonomy, lives in <a
            href="https://github.com/HelgeSverre/fedit/blob/main/CLAUDE.md">CLAUDE.md</a
          > in the repo. Phase notes for shipped work are in
          <a href="https://github.com/HelgeSverre/fedit/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md">CHANGELOG.md</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </section>
</Site>

<style>
  .arch-p {
    color: var(--fg);
    max-width: 75ch;
  }
  .arch-p code {
    color: var(--fg);
  }
</style>
